<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Aurora Climate</h2>
<p>For Aurora's cold climate, dual-fuel heat pump systems offer the best year-round efficiency, switching between electric heat pump operation in mild weather and gas furnace backup when temperatures drop below 25¬∞F. Look for heat pumps with HSPF ratings of 9.0 or higher and SEER ratings of at least 16. Traditional gas furnaces should have AFUE ratings of 90% or higher to maximize heating efficiency during Aurora's long winters. For cooling, 16-18 SEER air conditioning systems provide adequate efficiency for the moderate summer cooling demands, though higher SEER ratings offer better humidity control and comfort. Given that heating represents 60-70% of annual HVAC energy use in Aurora, investing in high-efficiency heating equipment provides the greatest return on investment.</p>

